  "text": "Next, we examined whether the D477G mutation affected the transcriptional level of RPE65 using real-time PCR. RPE65 mRNA levels were comparable between WT, heterozygous and homozygous KI mice (Supplementary Material, Fig. S1 ) consistent with prior data [CITATION_1] . To evaluate the ratio of transcribed WT and D477G mRNA, we collected 95 RPE65 cDNA clones from the RPE layer of heterozygous mice and sequenced them.",
